PRESS & MEDIA | Anvil Energy HOME ABOUT TEAM CONTACT PRESS & MEDIA More Use tab to navigate through the menu Press & Media Press Releases July , Anvil Channel closes $65MM Direct Loan to Certus Oil & Gas ​ HOUSTON, July , PRNewswire -- Anvil Channel Energy Solutions today announced final close of a USD$65,000,000 senior secured loan facility to Certus Oil & Gas, , supporting the acquisition of producing assets in central This transaction marks the first transaction undertaken by the new Anvil Channel direct energy lending ​ "We are excited to have successfully executed this transformative transaction with support from the Anvil team the creative capital solution structured by Anvil came at a critical time in our company s growth " said Rob Brady President and CEO of ​ Anvil seeks to solve the gap between bank lenders, which have largely pulled back from the micro and market in the and Canada, and the typically more expensive mezzanine and preferred equity ​ "We were particularly happy to provide a liquidity solution in this persistently challenging energy " Noted Cary Meadow, Chairman and CEO of Anvil "This transaction is a perfect representation of Anvil s thesis and mission - provide established producers with much needed acquisition and development capacity to meet their growth goals in a tight liquidity " ​ Proceeds of the loan were used to fund the corporate acquisition of Sitka Exploration , providing geographically and technically complimentary assets to the existing Certus ​ Anvil continues to seek strong sponsor partners with deep knowledge in the upstream E&P space who require acquisition, refinance and development capital for producing ​ Noted David O Driscoll, and President of Anvil Channel, "We are excited to partner with the Certus team to support their transformative acquisition and next phase of Our expanded investment mandate allows us to consider supporting proven management teams in Canada as well as in the , and we re delighted to get this inaugural transaction closed in an expedited " Echoing this sentiment James Avery said, "We believe our ability to stretch lend in this environment makes us an extremely competitive alternative to other sources of capital while maintaining a comfortable pricing level for the Company by tailoring the cost to fit production and and look forward to continuing to review new opportunities throughout the balance of the " ​ About Certus Oil and Gas Certus is a privately owned company that has been operating in central Alberta since ​ About Anvil Channel Anvil Channel Energy Solutions is a private direct lender focused on the upstream energy With offices in New York and Houston the company invests within tightly bound perimeters of value oriented oil and gas opportunities backed by several institutional More information is available on its website: http: www.anvilcp.com ​ April , Anvil and Boomerang Merge to Capitalize on Loan Demand for Middle Market Borrowers ​ HOUSTON, April , PRNewswire -- Boomerang Credit Fund, Channel Investments and the Anvil Energy Partners team today announced a business combination to deploy up to $300,000,000 via a static pool lending facility for upstream oil and gas The new company will be branded as Anvil Channel Energy The new private lender will originate new issue facilities for borrowers seeking between $10,000,000 and $100,000,000 for refinancings, acquisitions and development of energy The firm will combine origination, credit expertise and technical engineering leveraged to the Anvil team and ​ "We are excited about the prospects our combined teams offer in terms of addressing the largely unmet small and market for direct lending," said Cary Meadow, Executive Chairman of Anvil "We believe in the continued long term need for capital deployment to environmentally sound upstream energy " Echoing Meadow, James Avery, CEO of Anvil Channel said, "We look forward to the structural integration of our firms and coming to market with our first transactions in We believe that while renewable energy and alternative power solutions are an integral part of the global energy mix going forward, upstream oil and gas are still critical elements of the energy complex for the foreseeable " ​ President and CIO, David O Driscoll said, "The continued retrenchment of capital from the sector has resulted in a prolonged cycle we are excited to provide crucial liquidity to the market to facilitate the strategic initiatives of our " This sentiment was followed by his colleague and Head of Origination, Rob Lindermanis, who noted "we look to provide capital to companies positioned for growth and expansion in this challenging " The Company, headquartered in Houston, TX with offices in Los Angeles, CA and Stamford, CT is actively seeking opportunities in the domestic United States and ​ More information about the team and strategy is available at: http: www.anvilcp.com About Anvil Energy Partners The Anvil Energy Partners team entered the credit market

Blind Tiger is named for speakeasies during the The custom of illegal drinking establishments were to display stuffed tigers to alert potential patrons to the availability of illicit alcohol after The “tigers” were “blind” because the authorities, at least officially, did not know they These beverages are: Organic (cane sugar and honey) (RTD) Educational Pasteurized About Shop Our Story Locations Policy Contact (814) West , #334 ​Erie, PA   Shop our Cocktails - Blind Tiger Spirit Free skip to main content Shop Our Story About News Recipes Spirited Recipes Recipes Contact Locations Wholesale Discover Our Variatels Made with all natural and organic ingredients, Blind Tiger produces cocktails inspired by the and Learn more about our flagship Ward 8 Bee s Knees Sidecar Southside Blind Tiger Mixed Pack of 4 About Shop Our Story Locations Policy Contact (814) West , #334 ​Erie, PA   Welcome back to the Roaring - Blind Tiger Spirit Free skip to main content Shop Our Story About News Recipes Spirited Recipes Recipes Contact Locations Wholesale Our Story Welcome back to the Roaring In we opened a speakeasy style restaurant ( Room ) in the heart of downtown Erie, Over the years, our venue had become known for our classic However, in March of , at the onset of the pandemic, we were mandated to takeout only, and in Pennsylvania establishments were not legally allowed to sell At the time, % of our sales were bar sales, and like many, we had to pivot and One of the initiatives we launched were bottled versions of our cocktails – and the response was Through research we found a major underserved market – %+ of the US population does not drink alcohol (for a variety of reasons). And currently, there are only companies that produce drinks in the We also knew given our experience, there were not many creative alternatives in bars and restaurants to help those “feel part of the occasion” when not All of the flavor none of the Given our foray into the Prohibition era through our restaurant, as a passionate brand advocate, I wanted to stay with what we could capitalize on – our Prohibition Our team, led by Elizabeth Heffernan, created recipes for cocktails that would mirror the flavors of the original, but without the We wanted the consumer to have the defining flavors, even if they couldn’t have the We then worked with a variety of professionals to get that product and into As for the name “Blind Tiger?” That is what speakeasies were known as

Dark Star Quantum Lab | Quantum Technology | United States ROI Quantum Technology R&D Roadmap Deploying “killer apps” of Quantum Technology Quantum technologies are devices that utilize quantum physical features of entanglement and true randomness to produce advantages that conventional technologies Today, quantum technologies are commercially available in the form of Quantum processors: Information processors that provide computational speedup and optimized performance Quantum Randomness Generators: Network devices that can add a layer of true randomness and provable security to cybersecurity infrastructure ​ Dark Star Quantum Lab Inc . matches industrial problems with the right quantum technology ​ We are engaged in studies and product development across the business spectrum, around the globe . Development Roadmap ​ Dark Star is engaged in the development of software, hardware, and application domains for quantum ​ Cybersecurity - communication protocols for the internet and Finance - trading on the quantum Epidemiology - Quantum software toolkit for epidemiological modeling and data analytics ​ ​ Business Cases for Quantum Technology by Dark Star ​ ​ Perspective on quantum computing development ​ Quantum information technology and innovation: a brief history, current state and future perspectives for business and management ​ Quantum Prisoner’s Dilemma and High Frequency Trading on the Quantum Cloud ​ Financial Portfolio Management using Quantum Optimizer: The Case of Abu Dhabi Securities Exchange ​ ​ ​ ​ Research ​ Quantum processors computers today are faulty and not fully quantum physical and are therefore referred to as Noisy Intermediate Scale Quantum computers (NISQ). Dark Star research work envisions the next generation of quantum computers to be to a very high This first requires identifying the exact number of physical qubits into which abstract or logical qubits can be Our CEO answers this question here . ​ Consultancy Engagements ​ Dark Star is a consultant on quantum technology projects for industry leaders in the United Arab Emirates and ​ ​ Contact Parenting a child who is adopted involves much of the same love and understanding as any kind of parenting, but can also require additional awareness of issues of abandonment, attachment, shame, culture, trauma, (un)diagnosed medical, emotional, social issues, just to name a Parents of adopted children may feel overwhelmed by paperwork, how to navigate the educational medical systems Parents of adopted children may spend a lot of time explaining things to other people, not finding answers (we have answers!) Marriage can be tough in Marriages which experience the stress of infertility, the trauma of loss, varying degrees of partner life priorities or challenges with parenting can be even Individuals or couples who are considering creating or expanding their family through adoption (or other methods, do better when supported by mental health Ask about booking with a PonoRoots Supporting children and families in adoption Families that are built or added to through the adoption process, are in many ways just like any other family, and in crucial ways very While no two adopted people experience life, loss, or love exactly the same way, many tell us that certain challenges and issues arise that bear noting and ​ If you were adopted as an infant or an older child, if you have adopted and are or did raise an adopted child, or if you lovingly placed a child for adoption, you are a member of a unique Issues of abandonment, trauma, loss and grief, regret and guilt, attachment, control and relationship, identity, culture, fertility, and ancestral stories may be some of the topics warranting discuss or questioning in ​ In some cases members of the triad might not be sure what exactly is causing internal ​ We are here to listen and We won t you, or pathologize, we ll listen and learn from Once we ve figured out where the source of the pain may lie, we will get to ​ If you are interested in adopting a child or are seeking support services to help you with an adoption process, please contact our colleagues at A Family ​ ​ ​ ​ ​ For comprehensive adoption services, including home studies, and child placement, please contact A Family ​ Pono Roots Counseling Center at A Family Tree ​ King Street Honolulu, HI ​ (808) Hours: Monday - Sunday 8:00 AM to 8:00 PM ​ We are open seven days a week, hours a ​ Our goal is to serve In order to do that effectively, we need to be here when you need us . .. so here we are! Glutathione We live in a toxic world filled with dangerous chemical substances that threaten mankind, whether it be by inhalation, swallowing or direct Thanks to eras of evolution and research, it was finally discovered that a molecule, Glutathione, is an effective antioxidant tool that eliminates harmful substances from our Glutathione is a nutrient compound and one of the most versatile and important protective substances in the human It is found in different degrees within all tissues, body fluids, and organ It is a small protein, a tripeptide, present in almost all the cells of the body and a critical regulator of oxidative Glutathione protects cells from the action of very harmful compounds in the body: free Glutathione plays a very important role in the detoxification of the body, it helps regulate the function of many proteins and the activity of many enzymes, as well as the function of the immune Glutathione is called the Antioxidant Master for its powerful action to eliminate free radicals, and for its ability to reactivate vitamins C and E, which also helps in this No other compound has the capacity to do these jobs within the However, levels of Glutathione can be easily reduced when the body is exposed to stress, harmful elements found in food, the environment, medicines, alcohol, drugs, and Our body has an army to defend itself, a detoxification system which helps to keep us This defense system includes: the skin, which acts as the first line of defense against invasion the liver, which breaks down the toxins before they can begin to harm our body the kidneys, which filter and remove those toxins through the urine and the immune system, which essentially eliminates what other organs have Nonetheless, sometimes stress and external factors diminish certain key nutrients in the body that are important for When this happens, we can take supplements that compensate for this To give these vitamins an added boost and support our system, we can integrate the use of a Glutathione The growing interest in the scientific area around Glutathione – as one of the most important antioxidants – has awakened greater knowledge by young people, adults, and the Glutathione has become an increasingly pillar in the health field, demonstrating its benefits to maintain the body’s natural defenses and eliminate toxic free Although the human body can endogenously produce Glutathione, environmental factors such as pollution, exposure to ultraviolet light, stress, and a poor diet tend to produce a significant decrease in our natural reserves, making its supplementation much more necessary and The most recent scientific research has shown very positive results of the act

Outsourcing refers to hiring professionals outside a company to do a task which is normally performed In a traditional business model, a company would hire a person to perform a dedicated service internally – a call centre agent to take inbound In outsourcing, a company (such as OmTalent) will allocate you a team member to perfrom these functions as well as taking care of recruitment, hiring, payroll, management – in a much more cost effective If you are an insurance business, outsource your inbound support In your software company, perhaps you can outsource your technical Or if you own a law firm, you can outsource an administrative assistant to do all the What industires do we service? OmTalent currently services the following industries and we are constantly growing in line with our clients needs: Recruitment Insurance SaaS Medical Supplies Fundraising Solar Solutions Merchant Services Do I need internal systems to work with OmTalent? Yes you OmTalent provides and sets up a workstation for your outsourced team member and we’ll assist to integrate with all your systems and software (VOIP, CRM, Email). We make use of your internal systems for data privicy and simplicity OmTalent makes use of a seamless onboarding process where you will work closely with our integration This is to ensure your team is fully connected to the same systems and communication tools that you are currently How can I trust you and how long have you been around? We understand that outsourcing can sound complicated and far away (I mean where even is Johannesburg right 🙂 ) However, as we like to say, the proof is in the Over the last few years, we have successfully helped countless businesses accross the world in building well skilled, cost effective and successful outsourced Click here to read some case studies from our clients and reach out if you would like to speak to some of the companies we work with! Who facilitates training of my outsourced team? We suggest you allocate an internal training facilitator as knows your business as well as you and your current staff OmTalent provides additional sales and skill development training (at no additional cost) based on the team members How do I make sure that my team is doing their job? Firstly, your team are yours and you are welcome to implement any internal management You are also encouraged to engage with your team Furthermore, OmTalent assigns every team (no matter the size) an team lead who will be monitoring that they are meeting the KPI’s and metrics we’ll set out in the onboarding Furthermore, every client is assigned a dedicated account manager who will be the central point of contact for work, tasks, feedback, queries Additionally, we send out weekly and monthly feedback How can we help your business? Aside from cutting your expenses, OmTalent can also help reduce the stress from your internal employees caused by overwhelming You can delegate the small tasks to your remote team so and get back to the tasks only you can do! Swimming Daily Walks Jogs Massages Play Daily Walks Jog Walking or jogging with your dog not only helps strengthen their heart and improve circulation of the bloodstream but it also helps stimulate their brain with all the different sights, smells, and sounds of the beautiful outside Keep an eye on your dog’s hydration levels and always bring plenty of water with you, we recommend using a travel bottle for on the go hydration and Older dogs have more difficulty regulating their body temperature so it is crucial to have plenty of water in Swimming Arguably one of the best ways to Swimming will help your dog move its entire body against the resistance of the water, making it the ideal Swimming keeps the heart rate up while building endurance, muscle strength, and cardiovascular There are pools specifically for dogs, search it up online to find one in your local If you live by the coast, an afternoon at the dog beach will not only be so much fun but will also create forever memories for you and your pup! if your dog can’t swim or is afraid of water, there are underwater treadmill centers that can work as well! Massages Just like us, humans, a nice massage not only feels good but can also help dogs relax, increase oxygenation, relieve pain such as aches and sores, and most importantly improve joint There are a lot of different methods to help with different parts of the body! Play Every dog is a puppy at Channel that inner youth with fun activities that will help strengthen the muscles and joints of your Playing fetch is always a great activity to get the body For dogs with joint issues, it is recommended to roll the ball instead of throwing to make sure all 4 paws are on the Tug of war is another way to train the muscles in your dogs, just keep in mind to tug at the dog’s level to keep stress off their Obstacle courses, whether a makeshift, using your home furniture or an actual dog obstacle It’ll get your dog to move and use different parts of the muscles on the body to duck and weave through the Exercising not only promotes a healthier lifestyle but it also brings The mind and body must stay active in order to We hope you enjoyed this article, for more information please visit ! ❗❗ COMING SOON ❗❗ Our mission How it works Setup Testimonials FAQ Sign up SHOP More Did Dogs Develop Eyebrows To Communicate Better With Humans? posted by Shotaro Nabeya 12 2020 According to a study published by the National Academy of Sciences , puppy dog eyes are not natural expressions but a product of A team of researchers led by psychologist Juliane Kaminski, discovered that domestication has actually shifted the anatomy of dogs’ eyebrow muscles to help them communicate better with humans meaning their puppy dog eyes were a product of This study aimed to explore dogs’ facial muscles and compare them to their ancestors, The team examined the facial muscles of 6 different breeds of dogs, a Mongrel, Labrador, Bloodhound, Siberian husky, Chihuahua, and a German Shepard as well as four They were able to find out that the only difference the two species had was the levator anguli oculi medialis, the facial muscle responsible for controlling the inner “This movement makes a dogs’ eye appear larger, giving them a childlike It could also mimic the facial movement humans make when they’re ” Said Professor Bridget Waller, from the University of “Our findings show how important faces can be in capturing our attention, and how powerful facial expression can be in social ” We hope you found this article interesting, for more information please visit Recent Posts BLOG TERMS & CONDITIONS PRIVACY POLICY SHOP CONTACT Furry Tag© - All rights reserved Powered by dopweb ® This website uses cookies to ensure you get the best experience on our I accept   Furry tag │ Cloud Connected Pet Identification Tags ❗❗ COMING SOON ❗❗ Our mission How it works Setup Testimonials FAQ Sign up SHOP More Furry Tag - QR Digital Pet Tags Your Pet’s Safety Just Got Smarter! globally recognized, Validated by the Department of Defense and Department of Energy, CleanJoule’s proprietary production process converts biomass into a superior SAF molecule along with a rubber , yielding the only carbon negative, , full performance and percent SAF that can be used in a variety of commercial aviation engines without Cleanhill and Managing Partners Ash Upadhyaya and Rakesh Wilson will join CleanJoule’s board of Having previously served in leadership positions at KKR and Apollo, respectively, they bring decades of experience investing across the energy value “Cleanhill is on partnering with companies such as CleanJoule that are solving decarbonization challenges with timely, commercially viable approaches,” said Upadhyaya and “By rapidly scaling CleanJoule in Technology – TORmem Skip to content Menu Technology Products Applications Team Blog Contact Us Search Search for: Top Bar Email Email TORmem One Memory For All Menu Technology Products Applications Team Blog Contact Us Search Search for: Technology Our Challenge TORmem’s technology enables one memory for all, creating a single disaggregated memory bank for the whole To do this, we have to take protocols and technologies that were only designed to operate across a motherboard, and make them operate flawlessly for an entire rack of servers competing for access to the bank of disaggregated memory that can now be shared amongst This approach makes it possible for the mass market to create systems rivalling a typical supercomputer in Much of the difference between a large or hyperscale server cluster and a standard supercomputer today is the latter’s access to advanced memory access We aim to democratize this piece of the puzzle, making performance and cost at scale accessible to a whole new class of server Our products utilize, current and standards designed to provide , communication between devices across a motherboard, including PCIe Extending this interface across tens of servers in a rack won’t be easy, but we have developed some tricks to help us along the Towards One Memory for All We believe that creating a single, disaggregated bank of memory for the entire rack has multiple performance and cost benefits, especially when used at scale, such as: The memory supply chain is simplified and scale discounts are easier to obtain All servers in the rack can use the latest memory technologies, even over time Decommissioned servers will no longer take large amounts of memory with them Memory allocation across the rack can be controlled dynamically at a single point Solving Real Problems Moore’s Law As Moore’s Law approaches its limits, and the challenge of processing data locally and regionally becomes more acute due to the volume of data being generated, innovative solutions are required to continue improving performance for new and emerging The traditional approach has been to increase the compute capacity of the CPU, and to add more local memory but this no longer The amount of memory required for many use cases is growing, but the space and cost available for it on each local compute device, such as an individual server is How can we solve this? Computing (IMC) IMC is a model of computing where all of the data required for a particular task to be performed is held within This is opposed to a model, commonly seen in today’s compute systems whether at small or hyperscale, where there is insufficient memory to hold all of the data required for a complex task such as machine learning This results in the CPU, GPU or other processor needing to wait while data is fetched from a memory or storage source which is orders of magnitude slower than its local RAM, creating performance and efficiency Today’s Compute Systems In today’s compute systems, it is difficult to outfit an individual server with all of the RAM that it may need due to the technical capabilities of server chipsets including memory access limitations and slot count, as well as economic factors such as uncertainty about where a specific workload may be performed due to the use of abstraction layers common in cloud deployments, which may leave a single server that is with RAM The result is a hard choice between small amounts of fast memory which is IMC capable, and large amounts of slow remote memory in the form of storage technologies which are not fast enough to be suitable for Tomorrow’s Compute Systems Using TORmem technologies, a new tier of system memory can be added which provides a level of performance that is comparable to local system RAM, but with the same disaggregated, but model seen in slower types of memory or storage The result is a compute system, whether one rack or the combination of hundreds, which is no longer limited by the small capacity and inflexibility of local memory or the speed of traditional remote memory or storage The CPU, GPU or any other accelerator can be kept fully fed, allowing new workloads to be supported and for current workloads to operate more Optimizing System Costs By disaggregating large quantities of local system RAM from each server within the rack, the cost of each individual server can be reduced, as can the impact of its failure on the memory capacity of the entire server Much like the disaggregation of server storage that the industry has seen, we believe that the disaggregation of memory through our technology will bring about efficiency and design simplicity savings for systems large and Why Disaggregated Memory? One memory for A single disaggregated bank of memory for the whole Our technology enables Computing (IMC) at data center Optimize cost, accelerate current workloads, and enable new ones with Technology Product Applications Copyright © TORmem | Radiant Business by Firefly Themes   Team – TORme

Breaking Code Silence: From Pain to Purpose - Breaking Code Silence Skip to content Call Us Toggle Navigation About Us Who We Are Get Involved Volunteer With Us News Donate Previous Breaking Code Silence: From Pain to Purpose View Larger Image Breaking Code Silence: From Pain to Purpose Transforming Pain Into Purpose By Mel Gurr years ago, on October , , I was a depressed, conforming kid with undiagnosed That morning, two strangers arrived on my doorstep, and they transformed my life Without my knowledge or consent, I was taken to a remote facility called Cedar Ridge Academy, in Roosevelt, Utah – a place where I would spend most of the years between and , when I turned Cedar Ridge was a confirmedly abusive program, where physical, emotional, and sexual violence was just part of the fabric of daily It was a profitable , charging $5,600+ monthly, per child, and operated from until Where most American teenagers experience this life stage as a socially structured time of possibility, and the time to experiment with different interests, selves, and identities, children like me were institutionalized and tortured in the name of “treatment.” While there, we were prohibited from speaking, moving freely, and deprived of an One of my most poignant memories of Cedar Ridge Academy was a moment when my friend Rose and I, taking a break from farm chores, and hanging out near the fence surrounding the It was a rare moment when we were out of earshot of We talked about the Did anyone near Auschwitz care about the people suffering and dying in the concentration camps? While our experiences were worlds apart, as institutionalized kids in the , we wondered: Did anyone out there care about us? If anyone knew what was happening behind closed doors, would they intervene? Was help ever coming? We didn’t know it then, but help was coming – some years As adults, haunted by our own traumatic memories of Cedar Ridge Academy (along with other facilities), we became empowered by finding the TTI (troubled teen industry) survivor We took comfort in speaking with (or typing to) people who viscerally understood the sorts of moral injuries and lingering scars we carry from those years: fears of abandonment, trust issues, PTSD, anxiety, depression, low self esteem, and most especially, the recurring nightmares of being back at the program and unable to Being sent away was what I’ve come to understand as a “vital disjuncture:” an event that clearly cut my life in two: a relatively carefree “before” and a deeply painful “after.” Institutionalization had a devastating impact on my It has diminished my potential and delimited my future possibilities, in countless Each year, my body remembers my “sent away ” It has always been the worst day of my year, until Last night, on October , , while sitting in my pj’s in a darkened apartment in Lahore, I tuned into Paris Hilton’s livestreams via Twitter and Paris Hilton was joined by members of the Breaking Code Silence team, Caroline Cole and Vanessa Hughes, to introduce the Accountability in Congregate Care Having been producing content for survivors of institutional abuse for the last year and urging folks to take action, I was thrilled and shocked to see how rapidly we’d made progress towards our goals: from the unprecedented exposure after the September release of Paris’ documentary the protest at Provo Canyon School the massification of our community and incorporation as a nonprofit ’s legislative victories in Utah, Missouri, Oregon, and California and a spate of program Our movement against the troubled teen industry has made tangible, significant That being said, I am most excited by the emergence and articulation of a new movement, more broadly defined, which was just introduced to the public in press conferences held in Washington DC . With representatives from the troubled teen industry survivors movement, foster care survivors, disability rights groups, and the LGBTQIA community, with an espoused commitment to centralize racial justice in our mission, and making the lived experiences of children and families the shared foundation for our organizing work, I believe we have the potential to build something much more revolutionary and I believe this new, broad coalition, the movement against children’s institutionalization (residential treatment centers, group homes, juvenile detention centers, therapeutic boarding schools, ranches, and military ) has opened a new political and articulatory space capable of engendering deep, systemic By recognizing the shared roots of problems facing children in the United States– in discourses and practices that stigmatize, demean, and disbelieve them– we can finally recognize the central role played by multiple, disparate institutions in causing real In doing so, we can propose comprehensive solutions that promote the social, civil, and legal rights of children and families everywhere, inside and outside of During the press conferences, the speakers touched on

Background In , my spine began to compress, resulting in my inability to function independently and significantly increased reliance on personal assistant In On Becoming More Disabled , I described the shock of the change, my appreciation of the work attendants perform, and the luck I have living in California, where people with developmental disabilities receive the assistance they need regardless of their income or Attendants differ from caregivers in the same way the independent living model differs from the medical The medical model helps patients’ get better,’ feel better, be comfortable, The independent living model enables consumers to do what they want to do, live the life they want to It is a very different Attendants often perform extremely personal care tasks for minimum wages, no fringe benefits, little or no training, and a wide range of work They see us at our best and Their reliability, punctuality, and ability to understand cues are often critical to our Medical team members, including caregivers, usually only see us when we are ill or in a strange, confining, and alienating I am starting Abilicorp Foundation as a (c)(3) corporation whose mission will initiate and promote Disabled Owned Its 1 st project is developing and implementing the Abilicorp – Personal Assistant Services(ABPAS) in the Berkeley Oakland area, with plans to roll out its new model to many Our Unique Approach ABPAS is the latest agency to actualize the independent living The independent living model affirms that consumers (people with disabilities, elders, and their families) are the experts on their own needs and when those needs are met, can live the lives they want to ABPAS realizes this ideology by giving consumers as much control as they want over their attendant search, hiring, and management processes while providing attendants with living wages, healthcare options, training opportunities, and While other agencies charge high overhead fees for middle management services, ABPAS offers a variety of models for the attendant management process giving the consumer total agency in their search and over their Consumers can use the website tool for free and independently handle the entire attendant management process and the forms therein or consumers can hire and supervise an independence facilitator to coordinate attendant Alternatively, ABPAS can be the legal employer of attendants, responsible for payroll, tax filings, liability, , giving consumers as much or as few management responsibilities as they ABPAS will also offer the infrastructure for support circles: localized networks of attendants and consumers that share work schedules, rotate attendants, and respond to emergency or irregular Support circles allow attendants and consumers greater flexibility knowing they are held in a diversified network of support that can adapt in the face of emergencies or changes in Holding equity at its core, ABPAS will work with government agencies and healthcare plans to help ensure that people with disabilities and elders receive the assistance they need regardless of income and assets, and that attendants receive livable wages and We will work with consumers and their support circles to recruit attendants from colleges, universities, medical schools, community groups, religious institutions, and social We envision Contact Home About Us Our Story Projects RoboSub Summer of Technical Design Report Sponsors Contact Us Contact Email: Address: Memorial Dr W, Bethlehem, PA Follow us on Social Email Address Memorial Dr W, Bethlehem, PA Contact Us Copyright © a Theme by Gethugothemes This site uses By continuing to use this website, you agree to their I Accept   Our Story Home About Us Our Story Projects RoboSub Summer of Technical Design Report Sponsors Contact Us Our Story Our team was created in June of through Lehigh University’s Mountaintop Summer Experience Our mentor, Rosa Zheng, from Lehigh’s Electrical and Computer Engineering Department, chose the students involved to be a part of the research group called Autonomous Driving for Underwater Drones (ADUD). Our goal for the summer was to take a heavyweight version of the BlueROV2 from BlueRobotics and make it Over the summer we altered the hardware components of the drone, our biggest step being the addition of a ping For automation, we wrote code that was able to control the movement of the drone and looked into using OpenCV and Simultaneous Localization and Mapping (SLAM) algorithms to help with an automated navigation of the While we were mostly successful in our endeavor, we were inevitably unable to make our drone completely autonomous due to the hardware limitations of the BlueROV2 with the increasing demand of our By the end of the summer we decided we wanted to take what we learned about underwater robotics from the BlueROV2 and make our own drone that would better serve our hardware requirements for autonomous The concept of designing and building an autonomous underwater drone is very so we decided that we would join the RoboSub Competition to help challenge us and to give us a direction to go towards for our The process of making our group has heavily involved the restructure of our We transitioned our three teams of software, hardware and SLAM to be software, electrical, mechanical and To market our team better we decided to change our name from Autonomous Driving for Underwater Drones to Lehigh Underwater Robotics or LUR and developed a new logo and created a website and social media Our software team is implementing ROS code and algorithms into the drones’ automation instead of the Python scripts that we used over the More freedom has been given to our mechanical and electrical teams as they are designing the drone from scratch and are limited by the regulations of the competition, our budget and the needs of the software team for their Email Projects RoboSub Summer of Technical Design Report Sponsors Contact Us Technical Design Report Competition Strategy Team Makeup and workflow: The team is made up of four subteams: mechanical, electrical, software and business . Each team is responsible for designing certain components of the drone and collaborating so that each element fits together As a team, overarching goals are set, outlined by the RoboSub There is a general team leader and four leaders who are responsible for administration and defining and enforcing These are defined in order to achieve the larger goal by breaking it up into smaller tasks they get accomplished on a daily or weekly basis, and build upon themselves to accomplish the larger Software Strategy The main task of the software is to build on the work of the mechanical and electrical and integrate all the results to run In this process, we use several different methods to collaborate and achieve the results we These methods include training models for image recognition using YOLO, image processing, use of models in OpenCV, programming in Python (and then using C++ to improve efficiency later), and control of AUVs using ROS and Mechanical Strategy Team communication Due to part of our team being virtual we had to find a way to effectively communicate with the whole We solved this issue by having those who could be meet up everyday to work, and those that were virtual work remotely while having the whole team communicate ideas over Slack (a collaborative team app), thus allowing all members of the team to remain included and work together Settling on Designs Often when our team was designing a component for the chas

A social media campaign is a planned marketing effort that uses one or more social media channels to obtain a business What separates a successful social media campaign from everyday social media activity is the enhanced focus, specific targeting, and measurability that accompanies these Think of it like a political Candidates will establish their campaign goals and then carefully and expertly create a multistep process that will enable them to (hopefully) achieve those A social media campaign is essentially the same It is when a business establishes a certain goal, such as increasing brand awareness, obtaining new followers, or boosting sales, and then puts together a solid plan to achieve that Other common social media campaign objectives may be to: Obtain feedback from consumers Increase website traffic Increase phone calls leads Improve brand engagement Outperform competitors Convert impressions to active engagement How To Plan a Social Media Campaign Before you begin implementing your social media campaign, you’ll need to plan it out The first place you should start is by identifying a clear, measurable goal for your The means, message, and target audience all influence the interpretation of these Different demographics have different platform and content preferences, so choose the ones that best suit your target Once you establish your goal(s), you’ll want to acquire a baseline measurement of your desired metric so you can track changes and performance throughout the campaign’s Identify both where you’re at now and where you want to be by the end of the For example, if you want to increase your website traffic and are starting at an % conversion rate from your social media posts to website visits, you may establish your targeted metric (aka campaign objective) as being a 5% conversion In the planning phase of your campaign strategy, you’ll also want to be sure you have all the necessary tools in place to help track these Without a way to measure the successes or failures of your campaigns, you won’t have a clear picture of your There are several social media analytics tools out there that can help you with this, but we recommend you utilize Kiopi’s analytics PRO TIP: When you schedule your campaigns through Kiopi, you’ll be able to access a comprehensive analysis report that visually tracks your rate of engagement over time, including things like comments, likes, reactions, and How To Create a Social Media Campaign Once you have a clearer picture of your goals, target demographics, and how you will go about tracking your campaign’s Endorsements The Purple Poppy® Behind the Scenes Ways To Give Donate Honors and Memorials Media Press Shop Meet the Artist Susan Bahary is a sculptor of service animal One of the foremost artists specializing in honoring the bond, Susan Bahary, is a leader in raising awareness for the contributions and sacrifices of service animals and their In , Susan created our country’s first official and iconic war dog memorial, “Always Faithful,” unveiled at the Pentagon and installed at the Marine Corps War Dog Cemetery at the Naval Base on Susan’s sculptures of human, canine and equine subjects have been featured most notably on CNN, FOX news, NBC, and The Discovery Since , her Service Animal related works have had the honor and distinction of being located in museums such as the National Museum of the Marine Corps, UC Davis College of Veterinary Science, military bases such as Quantico, and other noted public installations Her works have been featured in many books and films including the first war dog feature film, MGM’s “Max.” Her international monuments include the War Animal Memorial, the first monument in the world to honor the nine million animals that died in the Western Front in WWI located in Pozieres, France The Australian War Animals Memorial located in the State’s Heritage Rose Garden, Queensland, Australia and the New Zealand War Animal Memorial at the National Army Museum of New THE PLEDGE monument at the Military Women’s Memorial at the gateway to Arlington National Cemetery with Susan This is the first monument in the nation’s capital to all women of the military past, present and Susan Bahary with Sully and the bronze of Sully for the George Bush Presidential Library and Museum commissioned by America’s – Photo Credit: James Chang America’s VetDogs Nationally, Susan’s bronze sculpture of our country’s first and most famous service dog, Stubby, with “Stubby Salutes” , can be viewed at the Veteran’s Memorial Park in Middletown, CT and a second casting is on display at the AKC Museum of the Dog in New York In December , Susan completed a bronze of President George HW Bush’s service dog “Sully” for the permanent collection of his Presidential Library and In , her monument “The Pledge”, featuring a woman soldier connecting with her devoted service dog as they ready themselves for their upcoming mission, was unveiled to great acclaim where it resides in the permanent collection of the Women’s Memorial in Arlington On Veteran’s Day , Susan’s bronze monument of the brave, fallen lead dog handler to SEAL Team 6, John Douangdara and his war dog, Bart, entitled, “Service and Sacrifice,” was placed permanently at the United States Navy Memorial in Washington , honoring all the men and women of the Sea Services, past, present, and Susan Bahary is excited to be the sculptor selected to create the National Service Animals To learn more about Susan and her work, please visit Make a Donation Today About Us Board of Directors & Advisors
